DB_HOST=localhost
DB_USER=root
DB_PASSWORD=agent p7
DB_NAME=bookstore
LOW_STOCK=5
FINE_PER_DAY=10
BORROW_FEE_PER_DAY=5


I assume that you have MySQL installed and setup and the env variables are done properly.
Note don't delete the .env it is the persistent memory of the program
there is a link to the first release of mine in there you can download the .7z from there extract it then go to the extracted folder right click click open in terminal (alternatively you can cd to that directory)  and paste "mysql -u root -p < sqldata.sql" enter your password and it should add the database and the testing values to the MySQL server.  Then you just double click the exe and you will be able to see the GUI and then it will first configure setting set them according to your system enter password and when the setting gets completed you will be able to se a menu of item you can move up or down by the up/down arrow key and press enter to select the option. And you have learned to operate it. If you encounter any error please report to me

you can also see a second installation way in my git repo 

I understand the fact that I have taken a lot of time but I took a bigger project then I should have so if you think this project is messy or took to much time have some leniency 

